# Manual & sticker docs must stay correct on every release

Before publishing a release (bumping `project_version` in `cloud-lamp.yaml` and running
`tools/release.sh`), re-verify `docs/user-manual.md` end-to-end against current behaviour:

- Button gestures/timings (§4), Wi-Fi setup steps (§5) and firmware update flow (§7)
  match the actual current firmware behaviour.
- Sticker field table (§2) matches `docs/device-credentials.md`'s Required/Recommended
  tables **and** the physically printed label (`docs/Label.lbx`) — if either changes,
  update both docs and the table together.
- Power-supply description, effect count/list, supported language list, and the
  permanent manual URL are still accurate. The manual URL
  (`https://danieldriessen.github.io/cloud-lamp/user-manual.pdf`) is printed on physical
  stickers and in the QR code — NEVER change it.

After any edit to `user-manual.md`, rebuild the PDF and commit both together:

```bash
python3 tools/build-manual.py
git add docs/user-manual.md docs/user-manual.pdf
```

The cover page's "Describes firmware vX.Y.Z" line is read automatically from
`cloud-lamp.yaml`'s `project_version` by `tools/build-manual.py` — never hardcode a
version number in the markdown source or the build script.

If a code change (button behaviour, Wi-Fi flow, update UI, effect list, supported
languages, sticker layout) could make any manual section stale, treat updating
`user-manual.md` as part of that change, not a follow-up task.
